00:59:11.943 --> 00:59:13.194
Did you want something?

686
00:59:13.236 --> 00:59:15.697
I just wanted to say
thank you.


687
00:59:15.738 --> 00:59:17.740
I'm honored
that you read my work.


688
00:59:18.533 --> 00:59:21.202
- Still waiting on that email.
- I'll send it today.


689
00:59:21.286 --> 00:59:24.414
Uh, no disclosure of my work
to any third party,


690
00:59:24.455 --> 00:59:25.915
as per the agreement.

691
00:59:26.791 --> 00:59:28.710
That includes Helene.

692
00:59:29.252 --> 00:59:31.004
Liam, you're welcome.

693
00:59:36.050 --> 00:59:37.885
You've been brought up
by the most revered writer


694
00:59:37.969 --> 00:59:38.886
in the country.

695
00:59:38.928 --> 00:59:41.180
So, why should I
give you a place?


696
00:59:45.935 --> 00:59:48.688
Well, uh, he's a writer.

697
00:59:48.730 --> 00:59:50.940
I want to be able
to learn to read work.


698
00:59:50.982 --> 00:59:53.568
You know,
to learn to criticize.


699
00:59:55.320 --> 00:59:57.280
How do you criticize
your father?


700
00:59:57.363 --> 00:59:58.948
I haven't read his work.

701
00:59:58.990 --> 01:00:00.617
That's not what I asked.

702
01:00:03.286 --> 01:00:05.955
I asked how you'd criticize
your father.


703
01:00:13.588 --> 01:00:15.340
Nothing can grow around him.

704
01:00:16.924 --> 01:00:18.885
My father never raised us.

705
01:00:20.637 --> 01:00:22.180
He just made us sick.

706
01:00:23.056 --> 01:00:23.973
How?

707
01:00:24.015 --> 01:00:26.267
Not caring is worse
than cruelty.


708
01:00:28.478 --> 01:00:29.854
What his son wanted
was his approval


709
01:00:29.896 --> 01:00:31.314
and he couldn't give it.

710
01:00:33.691 --> 01:00:35.777
- But don't you want it?
- No.


711
01:00:36.819 --> 01:00:38.363
Look where that got Felix.

712
01:00:42.825 --> 01:00:45.286
My brother didn't go
into the water to swim.


713
01:00:56.089 --> 01:00:57.674
But you could.

714
01:01:02.595 --> 01:01:03.805
I did.

715
01:02:23.342 --> 01:02:25.178
Whoo!

716
01:02:47.909 --> 01:02:50.119
I've been invited
to an 18th tonight


717
01:02:50.161 --> 01:02:51.871
and my mother is worried

718
01:02:51.913 --> 01:02:54.415
that it's gonna distract me
from our prep.


719
01:02:55.333 --> 01:02:56.834
I'm not worried.

720
01:02:57.585 --> 01:02:59.378
We've been working very hard.

721
01:02:59.420 --> 01:03:00.922
You're sick to death of me.-

722
01:03:01.005 --> 01:03:03.800
And I think he could do
with a night out of here.


723
01:03:04.133 --> 01:03:05.885
What would your father say?

724
01:03:05.927 --> 01:03:07.261
He's not here.

725
01:03:08.554 --> 01:03:09.847
Where are you gonna stay?

726
01:03:09.931 --> 01:03:11.140
At the flat.

727
01:03:11.724 --> 01:03:13.643
Well, get a cab
if you need to, please.


728
01:03:13.684 --> 01:03:16.687
Thank you.-

729
01:03:48.344 --> 01:03:49.846
Can I help?

730
01:03:50.012 --> 01:03:52.098
Yes. Ah.

731
01:03:56.853 --> 01:03:58.521
Thank you.

732
01:03:58.563 --> 01:04:00.022
Have you thought
about letting Bertie


733
01:04:00.064 --> 01:04:02.066
be somewhere else this summer?

734
01:04:03.276 --> 01:04:05.027
Well,
if Bertie's not here,


735
01:04:05.069 --> 01:04:07.238
there's no reason
for you to be.


736
01:04:23.212 --> 01:04:24.547
I love it, too.

737
01:04:25.590 --> 01:04:27.049
I didn't say that.

738
01:04:28.092 --> 01:04:29.510
You didn't have to.

739
01:04:37.059 --> 01:04:38.603
What did he do, Liam?

740
01:04:39.937 --> 01:04:41.606
Did he destroy you, too?

741
01:05:19.727 --> 01:05:21.187
What do you want now?

742
01:05:23.272 --> 01:05:24.857
To do my job.

743
01:05:25.983 --> 01:05:27.443
Help Bertie get out.

744
01:05:27.944 --> 01:05:29.320
And leave.

745
01:05:30.029 --> 01:05:31.322
Don't lie.

746
01:05:32.114 --> 01:05:34.283
I think you want
the same thing I do.


747
01:05:37.453 --> 01:05:38.996
And what's that?

748
01:05:42.750 --> 01:05:44.251
Why does he lock
my dead son's door


749
01:05:44.335 --> 01:05:46.212
if he's got nothing to hide?

750
01:05:47.797 --> 01:05:49.131
I wanna know.

751
01:05:51.092 --> 01:05:52.343
Don't you?

752
01:08:46.851 --> 01:08:49.103
Mr. Somers?

753
01:08:54.900 --> 01:08:56.193
The usual?

754
01:08:57.444 --> 01:08:58.654
Yes.

755
01:09:38.944 --> 01:09:40.196
How are you feeling?

756
01:09:40.237 --> 01:09:43.574
Like shit. And I can't find
that Bronte article anywhere.


757
01:09:44.158 --> 01:09:45.326
Liam.

758
01:09:45.367 --> 01:09:46.368
I need you in the study.

759
01:09:46.452 --> 01:09:48.454
- We're still working.
- Now.


760
01:09:57.630 --> 01:09:59.757
So, where is everything?

761
01:10:05.512 --> 01:10:06.889
- Fuck.
- What?


762
01:10:08.015 --> 01:10:09.558
This looks like a virus.

763
01:10:10.142 --> 01:10:11.435
It's...

764
01:10:12.102 --> 01:10:13.562
It's taken everything.

765
01:10:13.604 --> 01:10:15.189
Restore it
from the backup.


766
01:10:15.231 --> 01:10:16.440
Well, you never
disconnected the drive.


767
01:10:16.482 --> 01:10:17.566
It must have been running,

768
01:10:17.608 --> 01:10:18.859
so it's gone down too.

769
01:10:18.901 --> 01:10:21.528
- The other server.
- It's all...


770
01:10:21.612 --> 01:10:24.740
It's all gone,
Mr. Sinclair.


771
01:10:24.782 --> 01:10:26.242
What?

772
01:10:27.326 --> 01:10:28.953
I wanted to shut it down.

773
01:10:34.416 --> 01:10:35.376
It's the malware.

774
01:10:35.417 --> 01:10:36.877
It must have come
from my computer


775
01:10:36.919 --> 01:10:38.212
when I sent you the documents,

776
01:10:38.254 --> 01:10:39.463
the annotations.

777
01:10:39.505 --> 01:10:40.714
What?

778
01:10:40.756 --> 01:10:42.091
I am so sorry.

779
01:10:42.132 --> 01:10:44.635
So unlike you
to be so careless, darling.


780
01:10:46.929 --> 01:10:49.306
Especially when
it's taken you so long.


781
01:10:54.144 --> 01:10:56.021
But you've still
got the hard copy.


782
01:11:20.671 --> 01:11:21.964
Close that door.

783
01:11:47.364 --> 01:11:49.783
He must have left it
at the conference.


784
01:11:55.456 --> 01:11:57.708
Yeah. It's James Sinclair.

785
01:11:57.791 --> 01:11:59.043
Uh, could you put me through

786
01:11:59.126 --> 01:12:00.711
to the Conference Centre,
please?


787
01:12:01.211 --> 01:12:02.504
Yes, I'll hold.

788
01:12:16.018 --> 01:12:18.395
You've already
looked in there, darling.


789
01:12:18.479 --> 01:12:20.647
Well, it's not
at the conference.


790
01:12:20.689 --> 01:12:22.149
It's not at the hotel.

791
01:12:22.232 --> 01:12:25.319
Not in the car,
not in the house.


792
01:12:25.652 --> 01:12:27.613
Someone has taken my novel.

793
01:12:27.696 --> 01:12:30.074
- Someone here has it.
- Which one of you is it, hmm?


794
01:12:33.660 --> 01:12:35.746
Oh, you've taken it,
haven't you?


795
01:12:36.330 --> 01:12:37.498
Ah.

796
01:12:37.581 --> 01:12:39.917
Tucked it away somewhere,
have you?


797
01:12:40.542 --> 01:12:42.252
So neat and tidy.

798
01:12:42.669 --> 01:12:45.214
Where have you hidden it,
Bert?


799
01:12:45.255 --> 01:12:47.383
We all know
you're hiding something.


800
01:12:49.343 --> 01:12:50.594
Where is it?

801
01:12:51.678 --> 01:12:53.263
Where is it?

802
01:12:53.305 --> 01:12:54.598
- Where is it?
- That's enough!


803
01:12:54.640 --> 01:12:57.017
"It had been
overcast all morning.


804
01:12:57.601 --> 01:12:59.311
"But when
we were clear of the bay,


805
01:12:59.395 --> 01:13:02.106
"the sun split
the cloud bank in two,


806
01:13:03.148 --> 01:13:05.109
"and threw light
onto the water.


807
01:13:07.778 --> 01:13:09.530
"Thin films of petrol,

808
01:13:09.613 --> 01:13:11.281
"swirling rainbows.

809
01:13:11.365 --> 01:13:14.451
"I was unsteady on my feet
as I approached the bow.


810
01:13:14.493 --> 01:13:17.496
"Someone grabbed my arm,
stood me upright.


811
01:13:18.122 --> 01:13:21.583
"I hadn't known how heavy
her ashes would be."


812
01:13:21.667 --> 01:13:23.544
How much
do you remember?


813
01:13:25.587 --> 01:13:26.588
All of it.

814
01:13:26.672 --> 01:13:28.090
Bertie,
go get your things.


815
01:13:28.132 --> 01:13:29.716
- Now?
- Now, sweetheart.


816
01:13:29.800 --> 01:13:31.593
But you're leaving tomorrow.

817
01:13:31.635 --> 01:13:33.095
I'm giving you
the space you need,


818
01:13:33.178 --> 01:13:35.139
no distractions. Ellis.

819
01:13:35.597 --> 01:13:36.723
Bring me my bags, please.

820
01:13:36.765 --> 01:13:38.392
He knows
I didn't mean it.


821
01:13:38.434 --> 01:13:39.476
I need you here.

822
01:13:39.560 --> 01:13:41.395
- You need to write the book.
- I've written it.


823
01:13:41.437 --> 01:13:43.605
Then it shouldn't be
too hard to remember.


824
01:13:43.814 --> 01:13:45.065
Is Liam coming?

825
01:13:45.107 --> 01:13:46.817
Just carry on
like we've done.


826
01:13:46.859 --> 01:13:48.277
You'll be ready.

827
01:13:48.318 --> 01:13:49.736
Good luck, Bertie.

828
01:13:52.364 --> 01:13:53.991
He'll never get in.

829
01:13:55.451 --> 01:13:57.661
That's what you said
about Felix.


830
01:14:03.834 --> 01:14:06.753
- That's my work.
- That's the feeling.


831
01:14:09.840 --> 01:14:11.633
I married a writer.

832
01:14:13.469 --> 01:14:14.678
So write.

833
01:14:20.434 --> 01:14:22.311
Boys and their mothers, Liam.

834
01:14:22.394 --> 01:14:24.396
Bet you weren't
pampered like that.


835
01:14:24.438 --> 01:14:26.023
- No.
- Shall we?


836
01:14:34.781 --> 01:14:36.033
We use this.

837
01:14:37.534 --> 01:14:39.912
Won't need
to back this fucker up.


838
01:14:41.705 --> 01:14:43.207
This fucking place.

839
01:14:46.793 --> 01:14:48.545
You waiting for something?

840
01:15:08.273 --> 01:15:10.901
- Good start.
- We'll pick up tomorrow.


841
01:15:13.695 --> 01:15:14.988
Night, Liam.

842
01:15:42.349 --> 01:15:43.642
What was it?

843
01:15:44.393 --> 01:15:45.352
How did it go?

844
01:15:45.435 --> 01:15:46.853
- I remember...
- Oh, uh, ah...


845
01:15:52.526 --> 01:15:55.279
"But even from a distance,
I could read something absent


846
01:15:55.362 --> 01:15:57.864
"in her bearing, a frailty
that I hadn't seen..."


847
01:17:02.054 --> 01:17:03.639
I didn't write that.

848
01:17:04.848 --> 01:17:06.683
It's the end of Part Two.

849
01:17:06.725 --> 01:17:08.435
"These moments
rise up before me


850
01:17:08.518 --> 01:17:10.437
"like shards of light
in a shallow pool,


851
01:17:10.520 --> 01:17:14.149
"never joined for long enough
to tell the storm..."


852
01:17:15.776 --> 01:17:17.444
- I didn't write that.
- You're changing my work.


853
01:17:17.486 --> 01:17:19.821
- I'm not.
- Who's the fucking writer?


854
01:17:30.666 --> 01:17:31.917
Right.

855
01:17:33.460 --> 01:17:34.878
End of Part Two.

856
01:17:38.715 --> 01:17:40.175
Let's call it a night.

857
01:18:04.658 --> 01:18:07.244
You know,
your novel wasn't bad.


858
01:18:08.787 --> 01:18:09.955
Wasn't bad.

859
01:18:15.085 --> 01:18:17.337
She thinks I'm done.

860
01:18:18.130 --> 01:18:19.756
But we'll show her.

861
01:18:20.799 --> 01:18:22.634
We'll show her, Felix.

862
01:19:41.630 --> 01:19:42.964
Ellis, would you mind?

863
01:19:49.137 --> 01:19:50.722
Welcome home.

864
01:19:52.682 --> 01:19:53.975
We've been working.

865
01:19:54.518 --> 01:19:56.478
- So you're finished?
- Not yet.


866
01:19:57.604 --> 01:19:58.688
Better hurry up.

867
01:19:58.730 --> 01:20:00.524
You need to get started
on the next one.


868
01:20:00.607 --> 01:20:02.526
Where's Bertie?

869
01:20:02.609 --> 01:20:04.778
- In London.
- How is he?


870
01:20:05.111 --> 01:20:07.030
He's fine. Preparing.

871
01:20:07.948 --> 01:20:10.951
Darling, collect the bags
from the car, please.


872
01:20:11.034 --> 01:20:12.244
Oh, sure.

873
01:20:14.412 --> 01:20:17.916
Liam, can I see you
in the studio, please?


874
01:20:18.291 --> 01:20:19.417
Why?

875
01:20:20.001 --> 01:20:21.962
To extend our arrangement.

876
01:20:27.259 --> 01:20:28.885
His words,

877
01:20:28.969 --> 01:20:30.387
the ones you spoke.

878
01:20:30.929 --> 01:20:31.972
They're not his.

879
01:20:32.055 --> 01:20:33.348
They're my son's.

880
01:20:36.726 --> 01:20:39.980
Then why has it taken him
all this time to write?


881
01:20:41.273 --> 01:20:42.983
It wasn't finished.

882
01:20:44.192 --> 01:20:45.986
He gave it an ending.

883
01:20:46.236 --> 01:20:47.445
And?

884
01:20:50.073 --> 01:20:51.324
Hmm.

885
01:20:51.825 --> 01:20:53.285
Then I'd like you
to write one.


886
01:20:53.368 --> 01:20:54.661
The shorter the better.

887
01:20:54.744 --> 01:20:56.371
Consider this
your first commission.


888
01:20:58.665 --> 01:21:00.458
How soon
can you get this done?


889
01:21:02.043 --> 01:21:03.461
I'll start it now.

890
01:21:04.254 --> 01:21:05.463
Good.

891
01:21:07.090 --> 01:21:08.592
Better get on with it.

892
01:21:32.657 --> 01:21:35.368
Return to normality.

893
01:21:35.869 --> 01:21:38.163
We missed you, my love.

894
01:21:38.246 --> 01:21:39.998
Shall we
have some music?


895
01:21:40.040 --> 01:21:41.041
Of course.

896
01:21:41.082 --> 01:21:42.834
Some Schubert
for the homecoming.


897
01:21:42.918 --> 01:21:44.294
Liam, you choose.

898
01:21:45.128 --> 01:21:46.379
Ah.

899
01:21:49.382 --> 01:21:51.051
We're getting close.

900
01:21:51.134 --> 01:21:53.845
I'll call the publishers
tomorrow and let them know


901
01:21:53.887 --> 01:21:54.930
it's on its way.

902
01:21:54.971 --> 01:21:56.598
Well, I've already
been in touch with them


903
01:21:56.640 --> 01:21:59.100
- and your editor.
- What? I'll speak to them.


904
01:21:59.142 --> 01:22:01.394
- No, you won't.
- I'll deal with that.


905
01:22:01.436 --> 01:22:02.854
No more distractions.

906
01:22:04.105 --> 01:22:07.025
You just focus on finishing.

907
01:22:07.317 --> 01:22:09.027
You deserve to.

908
01:22:10.028 --> 01:22:12.030
You've been
held back too long.


909
01:23:02.998 --> 01:23:05.667
You don't mind
if I deliver this, do you?


910
01:23:13.925 --> 01:23:15.385
"And then...

911
01:23:16.011 --> 01:23:18.054
"And then she walked

912
01:23:18.763 --> 01:23:20.598
"along the shoreline...

913
01:23:23.977 --> 01:23:26.396
"as far as I could see...

914
01:23:27.397 --> 01:23:30.650
"her dress trailing in the...

915
01:23:31.443 --> 01:23:32.318
"The..."

916
01:23:32.402 --> 01:23:33.445
- "Wash..."
- "Wash!"


917
01:23:33.528 --> 01:23:35.405
"...of the tide."

918
01:23:35.822 --> 01:23:37.073
"The waves

919
01:23:37.741 --> 01:23:41.745
- "took her footprints."
- "Footprints."


920
01:23:43.413 --> 01:23:49.419
"I... followed... after."

921
01:23:52.881 --> 01:23:55.759
"The end."

922
01:24:00.055 --> 01:24:00.972
We did it.

923
01:24:01.056 --> 01:24:02.515
It's done.

924
01:24:03.016 --> 01:24:05.518
We fucking did it!-

925
01:24:05.602 --> 01:24:06.770
Oh.

926
01:24:08.229 --> 01:24:10.315
Oh.

927
01:24:10.356 --> 01:24:12.317
Come here. Come here.

928
01:24:14.903 --> 01:24:17.947
Steady.

929
01:24:18.031 --> 01:24:19.282
You and I...

930
01:24:20.325 --> 01:24:22.243
we finished that bastard.

931
01:24:22.327 --> 01:24:25.288
- Okay.
- This calls for a celebration.


932
01:24:28.958 --> 01:24:30.335
All gone!

933
01:24:34.005 --> 01:24:35.924
Oh.

934
01:24:38.384 --> 01:24:40.720
Congratulations, Mr. Sinclair.

935
01:24:41.179 --> 01:24:42.388
Cheers!

936
01:24:51.106 --> 01:24:52.816
I called it   Rose Tree,

937
01:24:53.399 --> 01:24:55.276
because I wrote it for him.

938
01:24:56.861 --> 01:24:58.404
He was the only one.

939
01:24:59.072 --> 01:25:01.658
The only one who understood.

940
01:25:03.910 --> 01:25:05.411
I found him, you know.

941
01:25:07.622 --> 01:25:09.541
Not his mother, not Bert.

942
01:25:09.582 --> 01:25:11.709
Both had better things to do.

943
01:25:11.793 --> 01:25:15.171
I dragged him
out of that water.


944
01:25:15.964 --> 01:25:19.217
- He had a real talent.
- I tried to help him.


945
01:25:19.259 --> 01:25:21.678
Constructive criticism,
like I gave you.


946
01:25:22.804 --> 01:25:26.349
But he was weaker
than I thought.


947
01:25:28.059 --> 01:25:29.310
Depressive.

948
01:25:31.354 --> 01:25:32.730
If I'd known...

949
01:25:32.772 --> 01:25:35.233
he would have
done something that stupid...


950
01:25:36.151 --> 01:25:37.485
I wouldn't have said...

951
01:25:41.489 --> 01:25:43.116
...anything to him.

952
01:25:48.037 --> 01:25:49.289
Right.

953
01:25:49.998 --> 01:25:52.542
You, me, swim.

954
01:25:52.584 --> 01:25:54.043
Right now!

955
01:25:54.085 --> 01:25:56.337
No excuses. Come on, Liam!

956
01:25:56.421 --> 01:25:57.714
Come on!

957
01:26:02.594 --> 01:26:05.889
Exercise makes the day, Liam.

958
01:26:08.391 --> 01:26:09.934
Are you coming in?

959
01:26:09.976 --> 01:26:12.395
- Of course.
- Good man.


960
01:26:12.478 --> 01:26:14.564
Now, how...

961
01:26:15.064 --> 01:26:15.899
How...

962
01:26:15.982 --> 01:26:19.319
How... How do you
want to be credited?


963
01:26:19.402 --> 01:26:22.405
- How about "author"?
- How's that?


964
01:26:23.156 --> 01:26:24.282
It must have hurt you.

965
01:26:24.365 --> 01:26:26.242
When you saw   Rose Tree
for the first time,


966
01:26:26.326 --> 01:26:28.453
of course,
you wished it was yours.


967
01:26:28.494 --> 01:26:31.206
- I did, too.
- He was better than both of us.


968
01:26:31.247 --> 01:26:33.082
Rose Tree   is mine.

969
01:26:33.166 --> 01:26:34.584
I wrote the book.

970
01:26:35.293 --> 01:26:37.462
No. Felix wrote it.

971
01:26:37.503 --> 01:26:40.673
You stole it. But I bet you...

972
01:26:41.299 --> 01:26:43.259
he came to you for advice.

973
01:26:43.343 --> 01:26:45.303
And I bet you,
you crushed him.


974
01:26:45.386 --> 01:26:46.804
He's my son.

975
01:26:46.846 --> 01:26:48.890
I gave him
every word of that novel,


976
01:26:48.932 --> 01:26:50.725
and when he couldn't
see it through to the end,


977
01:26:50.767 --> 01:26:52.185
I did.

978
01:26:53.394 --> 01:26:56.147
You know, I found
the original on his server.


979
01:26:56.231 --> 01:26:57.315
And I wiped it.

980
01:26:57.398 --> 01:27:01.319
Yours, too. I threw
the printout into the lake.


981
01:27:02.487 --> 01:27:03.696
Helene knows.

982
01:27:04.364 --> 01:27:07.158
That's why she asked me
to write it and finish it.


983
01:27:08.326 --> 01:27:10.370
'Cause she knew
you'd ruin that novel.


984
01:27:10.411 --> 01:27:12.330
She begged me
to save it from you.


985
01:27:12.413 --> 01:27:13.998
You're no writer.

986
01:27:14.082 --> 01:27:15.625
That's not
what your wife thinks.


987
01:27:16.376 --> 01:27:18.544
You don't fucking know her.

988
01:27:19.462 --> 01:27:21.381
I know what she tastes like.

989
01:27:25.635 --> 01:27:26.886
What?

990
01:27:45.196 --> 01:27:47.156
Drown. Drown!

991
01:27:47.240 --> 01:27:48.449
Drown, you...

992
01:27:50.410 --> 01:27:53.538
Drown! Drown, you fucking...

993
01:28:08.594 --> 01:28:10.388
Ah!

994
01:28:20.231 --> 01:28:21.566
You coward!-

995
01:28:21.649 --> 01:28:23.526
You fucking coward!

996
01:28:41.044 --> 01:28:42.503
Ah,
we'll get that seen to.


997
01:28:42.545 --> 01:28:44.547
And I'll get you
some dry clothes.


998
01:31:11.861 --> 01:31:13.154
Is he okay?

999
01:31:21.037 --> 01:31:23.289
I've read them both,
and you were right.


1000
01:31:23.331 --> 01:31:25.208
Yours is the superior ending.

1001
01:31:27.710 --> 01:31:29.045
His is a...

1002
01:31:29.545 --> 01:31:30.880
great shame.

1003
01:31:32.423 --> 01:31:34.133
You can get started now.

1004
01:31:47.271 --> 01:31:50.566
I want to thank you
for everything you've done.


1005
01:31:51.943 --> 01:31:54.779
- You were perfect.
- Remarkable, even.


1006
01:31:56.822 --> 01:31:58.908
This is how the story goes.

1007
01:31:59.450 --> 01:32:00.535
My husband,

1008
01:32:00.576 --> 01:32:03.829
after completing
his latest novel...


1009
01:32:03.913 --> 01:32:07.124
drowned himself in the lake
where his son died.


1010
01:32:08.125 --> 01:32:12.463
We'd been worried about him
and his drinking for a while.


1011
01:32:13.172 --> 01:32:15.758
We did all we could
to save him...


1012
01:32:15.841 --> 01:32:18.135
...but it was too late.

1013
01:32:21.889 --> 01:32:24.350
- What?
- And you, Liam,


1014
01:32:24.433 --> 01:32:25.851
you were never here.

1015
01:32:29.855 --> 01:32:31.357
You signed an NDA.

1016
01:32:31.399 --> 01:32:32.858
If you choose
to break our agreement,


1017
01:32:32.942 --> 01:32:34.694
there is another story.

1018
01:32:35.820 --> 01:32:39.782
Two witnesses can testify
to the murder of my husband


1019
01:32:40.449 --> 01:32:41.951
by an obsessive fan,

1020
01:32:42.410 --> 01:32:43.661
a would-be writer,

1021
01:32:43.703 --> 01:32:44.870
that took a teaching job

1022
01:32:44.954 --> 01:32:47.331
so he could be
close to his idol,


1023
01:32:47.415 --> 01:32:48.541
and who snapped

1024
01:32:48.583 --> 01:32:51.627
when his hero told him
something he didn't like.


1025
01:32:53.588 --> 01:32:55.756
I don't want
any kind of scandal,


1026
01:32:55.840 --> 01:32:57.341
but if I have to,

1027
01:32:57.383 --> 01:33:01.012
I will make you
the villain of this story.


1028
01:33:09.353 --> 01:33:11.063
This was never for Bertie.

1029
01:33:12.356 --> 01:33:14.900
I brought you here
to get me the truth.


1030
01:33:15.776 --> 01:33:18.529
And when I knew,
my husband was always gonna


1031
01:33:18.613 --> 01:33:20.239
join my son in the water.

1032
01:33:21.198 --> 01:33:24.118
Rose Tree   will be
their legacy.


1033
01:33:28.164 --> 01:33:29.749
The ending.

1034
01:33:33.002 --> 01:33:34.754
I wrote the ending.

1035
01:33:37.548 --> 01:33:39.091
You have to give me that.

1036
01:33:42.720 --> 01:33:44.555
I wrote the fucking ending.

1037
01:33:44.639 --> 01:33:46.390
And I'm grateful.

1038
01:33:46.474 --> 01:33:48.643
That's why
I'm giving you a chance.


1039
01:33:49.518 --> 01:33:50.770
I'm going to call
an ambulance,


1040
01:33:50.853 --> 01:33:53.064
and I don't wanna have
to explain your presence


1041
01:33:53.105 --> 01:33:54.565
when it arrives.

1042
01:33:54.607 --> 01:33:57.193
Much better that you
never existed at all.


1043
01:34:00.529 --> 01:34:02.365
My version of events

1044
01:34:02.823 --> 01:34:04.367
is the only version.

1045
01:34:05.493 --> 01:34:06.952
You can see that.

1046
01:35:52.641 --> 01:35:55.895
- You have talent.
- You just needed a story.


1047
01:35:59.148 --> 01:36:00.441
Tell Bertie...

1048
01:36:05.112 --> 01:36:06.822
Don't tell Bertie.

1049
01:36:14.455 --> 01:36:16.499
The gates will close
behind you.


1050
01:38:06.275 --> 01:38:07.568
Hello.

1051
01:38:07.651 --> 01:38:10.112
Liam Somers' story
of a fading patriarch,


1052
01:38:10.154 --> 01:38:12.072
presiding over
a grief-stricken family


1053
01:38:12.114 --> 01:38:14.867
has been described
as one of the most striking


1054
01:38:14.950 --> 01:38:16.535
debuts of the year.

1055
01:38:17.161 --> 01:38:19.788
Here with us
to discuss his first novel


1056
01:38:19.830 --> 01:38:21.290
is the author.

1057
01:38:23.000 --> 01:38:24.960
Thank you
for joining us, Liam.


1058
01:38:27.630 --> 01:38:29.173
Thanks for having me.